eatures that are CL 30 and below to be nerfed. Armor removed, stats changed. So whats left? You cant even call out 2 Giant Crystal Snakes at the same time as a MASTER CREATURE HANDLER. Wow... its so worth it now isnt it? Goodbye to the combos. <br>
<br>
Did I mention the CL adjustment of creatures above CL 30? Oh yeah, and HAM adjustments. So you can probably say goodbye to dual Graul Maulers or dual BDQs. Oh but we get maounts... Ooooo...a big slow lumbering pile of manure that doesnt help at all in combat and isnt any faster, AND it counts against your max CL and number of pets out. How thrilling... /yawn.. no really...it is.<br>
<br>
How does a Graul Mauler with 5k HAM, no armor, and resists lowered by 30% or more grab ya? No, this isnt confirmed, but how do you like the sound of it? Does it excite you and make you want to press onward to being a Master CH? where you can only call ONE (1) of them at a time. Oh the excitement... I think I got a chubby.<br>
<br>
I logged on for the first time in about a week last night, just to go patrol around Anchorhead and kill some Imperials. Really the only fun thing left for me to do in the game. I called out my BDQs and stood there thinking back to the day I tamed them. I realized that each and every pet in my datapad is a personal achievement for not only my character, but for me as well. Everyones experience in taming is different. Everyone uses different methods, etc. <br>
<br>
Some people are lucky enough to run up hit tame and get the baby is a couple of tries, some arent so lucky. I am one of those players that had to earn his pets. I tamed every single one of them myself(except a Gurreck I bought long long ago before the CL changes and I kept in my pad). I can remember each and every tame of my pets. I dont have anything lower than a CL 32 in my pad, and my pad is full as a Master CH.<br>
<br>
Im not going to get into the politics of buying -vs- taming, but I earned my pets the hard way. I crawled around for hours after my BDQs and my Maulers. I searched all over hte Prison area on Dathomir for 3 friggin hours looking for Grauls. My Gaping Spider Hunter was no pushover to get either. Some babies just dont want to be tamed. <br>
<br>
Toxic Merek Battlelord, Delerious Merek Avenger, Merek Assassin, 2 Riverside Sulfur Mynoks, 2 Graul Maulers, 2 Bloodseeker Mites, 2 BDQs, 2 Mountian Squills, a Gurreck, a Gaping Spider Hunter, and Spined Snake Recluse I tamed for a dancer that wanted a pet for her act.<br>
<br>
And I'll be able to use none of them in a combo ever again after this patch. It IS a nerf. It DOES hit the Master CH, despite what Thunderdork said. Giving us the ability to call on specials is nice, but its certianly not worth the loss we are taking.<br>
<br>
Sure, I may be able to go out and solo Kimos on Lok...but I never did. I might be able to solo ATSTs, and I have tried and failed many times, but I dont want to have to take Medic skills to do it. I think the only things Ive done solo that was really amazing, even to me, was to solo 6 Grauls at once. Including a Frenzied, 2 Maulers, and 3 regular Grauls. It was an accidental aggro from my pet I had out. They went after him and myself but we managed to take em all down. I suffered a mind bleed and 2 incaps for it, but I beat an entire nest of Grauls down by myself. It was pretty cool for me at the time, it was alot of fun, but was it so overwhelmingly overpowered that it deserves everyones hate? No. The simple answer to "How did you do it" is Grauls die easy. Nobody seems to know this about them. They die fast to a LLC. Ive killed lots of Imperial Graul Pets with just a couple shots. Electricity nails em hard... It wasnt an overpowering thing from my CH tree that killed them. It was my LLC from my BH tree that did. <br>
<br>
So they will nerf the CH profession. And yes it IS a nerf. But that doesnt change the fact that I can still 1 shot players in PvP, or I can mind shoot them into nothingness with my 200+ damage Scatter Pistol. My pets were never a threat in PvP because I didnt rely on them as such. My 2 BDQs are my PvP pets. I can send them after a single person or multiple people at the same time, and most of the time the other player will panic and shoot the pets, while I run up and blast them with my LLC. They were a distraction to the easily spooked player, nothing more. Their damage wasnt so huge that I could actually rely on them to kill another player. But thats just me. I tend to be somewhat more honorable in PvP than most people. It is a game afterall, and its supposed to be fun.<br>
<br>
For me, this nerf will take out that much more fun. We should all be sad. Even the Non CH should be sad. Some of them look at it as a revenge/grudge thing and will gloat over the fact that the mighty CH has fallen. But they should mourn because thats just more content gone from a game that is already achingly dull from lack of content.<br>
<br>
Enjoy. I however refuse to pay for it anymore. I will not be a SOE victim and watch them destroy the movies and worlds I grew up to love so much. LucasArts should be ahamed for letting SOE go this far with it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
