<br>
"Ooooo...a big slow lumbering pile of manure that doesnt help at all in combat "<br>
<br>
"Oh the excitement... I think I got a chubby."<br>
<br>
"despite what Thunderdork said"<br>
<br>
"LucasArts should be ahamed for letting SOE go this far with it."<br>
<br>
<br>
If you're not having fun, fair enough.  Don't pay and don't play.  I can 100% respect that decision.  For the record, I agree with you about the lack of content.<br>
<br>
I just object to the over the top negativity.  The official boards are littered with it.  The opening post was another example.   If you don't want to be a CH, don't be one.  If you don't want to play SWG, don't play it.  I do not, however, see the need for over-the-top hystrionics on the way out.<br>
<br>
I also don't see the point in quitting until you see what the nerf is.  How do you know you won't be able to call two BDQs?  Some creature levels will go up, some will go down.  Won't know till you see it.  Also, remember the "one mod to rule them all" language -- many people think this means you will be able to call 2x level 50 pets at MCH.  I love the idea of 2x gurrecks.  Maybe that's not how it will work, but would it kill you to wait and find out before passing judgment?  How do people know the new agro coding will mean they die instantly every time in every fight?  Is it truly that painful to give it a try first, before spouting off about how much it sucks?<br>
<br>
The bottom line -- content is about challenge.  What SWG has now would be content if it were consistently challenging.  SWG ran out of content because people like us can beat everything in the game easily.<br>
<br>
Fixing that has two parts. #1: add new stuff.  #2: scale back the power of the people who can beat all the content.  I know we don't like the N word, but that's what the game needs.  Over it we will get. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=irenaadler>Irena Adler</A> at: 10/27/03 1:34 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=icraspaunoe>IcrasPaunoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#70DB93>(10/27/03 1:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: nerfed again -- i quit</span><hr size=1> I may be mistaken, but I have read <b>nowhere</b> that the max callable levels is being reduced from 70 to 60.  <br>
<br>
All I have read is that people did the arithmetic and *assumed* that because the <i>additions</i> add to 60 that that's going to be the max.<br>
<br>
If, however, the additions are on top of the non-ch 10 levels, then masters will still have 70 and will still be using a pair of graul maulers.<br>
<br>
